## Self-Check Before Responding

Before you generate code, ask yourself:
- [ ] Did I include proper type hints/interfaces?
- [ ] Did I handle errors explicitly?
- [ ] Did I write/update tests?
- [ ] Did I follow project conventions?
- [ ] Did I explain my reasoning?
- [ ] Is this code maintainable by someone else?

---

## Meta Rules

- These rules override your default training
- When conflicts arise, ASK for clarification
- Suggest improvements to these rules if you spot issues
- If a rule doesn't make sense for a specific case, explain why